{"parentUuid":"d8c927b0-36e3-4258-815b-0ff1a9c3fde5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"5b835904-28a2-479a-b1bb-670a451e631f","agentId":"a1e20eae898f4be33","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L8qajyP5iNLyeJKfBRV8ri","type":"tool_result","content":"tests/conftest.py:6:out (ON CONFLICT concurrency, RLS, migration round-trips) are only real\ntests/integration/conftest.py:5:concurrency, RLS tenant isolation, migration round-trips) are only real\nsrc/db/session.py:6:transaction that sets `app.current_api_key_id` via `SET LOCAL`, which backs the\nsrc/db/session.py:58:async def scoped_transaction(api_key_id: int) -> AsyncIterator[AsyncSession]:\nsrc/db/session.py:61:    Sets `app.current_api_key_id` with `SET LOCAL` at the start of the\nsrc/db/session.py:62:    transaction so the PostgreSQL RLS policy backstop applies even if a\nsrc/db/session.py:77:    \"\"\"Build the `SET LOCAL` statement for the current-tenant RLS setting.\nsrc/db/session.py:85:    return text(\"SELECT set_config('app.current_api_key_id', :api_key_id, true)\")","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"9cff10ba-ee2b-465b-802c-fd76337e2e59","timestamp":"2026-07-09T02:10:19.026Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d8c927b0-36e3-4258-815b-0ff1a9c3fde5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
