read, not just the app's own echo).\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC3\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_ingest_key_forbidden\", \"reason\": \"Ingest-scoped key gets 403 code=forbidden.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC4\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_requires_auth\", \"reason\": \"Both missing and malformed Bearer tokens get 401.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC5\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (parametrized) + tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_validation_rejections\", \"reason\": \"0/-1/-1000/non-integer limit, unknown field, and bad customer_id all assert 422 validation_failed at both the unit-schema and endpoint layers.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC6\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_quota_is_tenant_isolated + tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py (both tests)\", \"reason\": \"The endpoint test proves the app-level api_key_id scoping keeps two tenants' rows independent. Independently added this session: test_quotas_rls_backstop.py proves the DB-level RLS BACKSTOP itself (not just the app filter) -- it connects as a provisioned NOBYPASSRLS role (mirroring the production meterly_app role, not the testcontainers superuser, which always bypasses RLS) and issues queries with the api_key_id predicate REMOVED ENTIRELY (the primary control disabled), asserting the RLS policy alone still confines reads/updates to the caller's own tenant, and that an unset tenant setting fails closed (zero rows) rather than defaulting open. This satisfies the adversarial-test-shapes requirement that a backstop control must be proven with the primary control off, not merely declared.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC7\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_no_quota_is_unlimited\", \"reason\": \"No quota row -> 201 for a very large quantity, no regression.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC8\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_under_limit_accepted\", \"reason\": \"R+Q<=L -> 201, rollup total verified via direct SQL read.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC9\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_over_limit_429_and_no_partial_write\", \"reason\": \"429 quota_exceeded + Retry-After >= 1s; direct SQL proves the rejected event left no row and the rollup only reflects the accepted event (transaction rolled back).\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC10\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_empty_window_q_gt_l_rejected\", \"reason\": \"First event in an empty window with Q>L -> 429; direct SQL proves zero rollup rows created.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC11\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_replay_over_quota_returns_200_no_usage\", \"reason\": \"A replay after the quota is lowered below the accumulated total still returns 200 with idempotent_replay=true and event_count stays 1 (quota never consulted on replay).\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC12\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_midwindow_change_takes_effect\", \"reason\": \"Lowering L below the already-accumulated R blocks the very next POST (429) -- fresh-read-per-request proven.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC13\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py::test_concurrent_posts_never_exceed_limit\", \"reason\": \"20 concurrent distinct-idempotency-key posts against L=10 land exactly 10 winners/10 rejections (429 quota_exceeded), and the final rollup total via direct SQL never exceeds L -- asserts the loser's outcome, not merely a single-winner count.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC14\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_throttle_precedes_quota_distinct_codes\", \"reason\": \"Tier-2 throttle fires first (code=rate_limited) via the full request lifecycle (not a unit test of the key generator); a genuinely quota-exceeded call on a separate untouched-throttle key returns the distinct quota_exceeded code.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC15\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_rate_limited_per_principal\", \"reason\": \"Two admin principals sharing one client IP (10.0.0.9) get independent Tier-2 buckets -- the discriminating two-principals-one-IP shape, not a same-owner-different-IP weak form.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC16\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py::test_0003_roundtrip_schema_and_constraints\", \"reason\": \"Seeds 2 api_keys rows + a quotas row, runs up->down(0002)->up, asserts: quotas table (create-migration) is fully absent after down (schema-only reversibility, no row-survival claim); the 2 pre-existing api_keys rows survive with scope resetting to the 'ingest' default (expand/contract add-column contract); and after re-up, every constraint (PK duplicate, FK to nonexistent api_key, CHECK limit>=1 for 0 and -5, and api_keys.scope CHECK) is independently re-driven and rejected -- not merely asserted present in a schema dump.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC17\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_seed_api_key_script.py::test_admin_flag_sets_scope\", \"reason\": \"--admin sets scope='admin'; omitting it defaults to 'ingest'.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC18\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_injection_rejected_at_boundary + tests/test_schemas_quotas.py::test_rejects_injection_and_oversized_customer_id/test_rejects_invalid_metric (+ Hypothesis property test)\", \"reason\": \"SQLi/path-traversal/CRLF/oversized payloads in customer_id and metric are rejected at the Pydantic boundary (422) before reaching quotas_repo's parameterized text() sinks; the Hypothesis property test additionally proves any customer_id that DOES parse matches the anchored allowlist over generated inputs, not fixed examples.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC19\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_rejection_is_logged_without_totals + tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_upsert_and_forbidden_logged\", \"reason\": \"quota.rejected (WARNING, no current_total/limit fields), quota.upsert, and quota.forbidden are each asserted present in structlog JSON stdout.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC20\", \"covered\": false, \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py::test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_under_50ms\", \"reason\": \"The test runs a real grafana/k6 Docker load (500 target rps, 15s measurement) against the quota-active POST /v1/events path and computes a true nearest-rank p95 over raw per-request samples (5493 samples, all 201s) -- but the test itself only asserts sample_count>0 (weak form), not the 50ms budget. Measured p95 this run was 3362.32ms, far exceeding the 50ms budget -- and substantially worse than this same host's baseline (no-quota) p95 of 83.55ms on the pre-existing AC6 ingest test, so this is not attributable solely to the known Docker-Desktop/Windows host.docker.internal overhead already flagged as a deferred finding on feature 1 (see MEMORY feature1_shipped_findings) -- the quota FOR UPDATE read-and-decide path appears to add substantial latency under sustained concurrent load across 50 customer buckets. Left uncovered rather than fabricating a pass; routes to debugging/human review.\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC21\", \"covered\": true, \"test\": \"tests/test_dast_context_documented.py::test_bearer_split_token_auth_context_is_documented + tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_openapi_exposes_put_quotas\", \"reason\": \"The served /openapi.json includes PUT /v1/quotas, and the DAST auth-context doc test confirms the Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret> scheme is documented; docs/system_architecture.md documents the admin test-key requirement (seed_api_key.py --admin).\" },\n      { \"id\": \"AC22\", \"covered\": false, \"test\": null, \"reason\": \"ASVS reconciliation is the security stage's deliverable, not a test-suite assertion.\", \"delegated\": \"security\" }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"resilience\": {\n    \"migration_roundtrip\": \"pass\",\n    \"property_tests\": 1,\n    \"concurrency\": \"pass\"\n  },\n  \"perf\": {\n    \"budget\": { \"p95_ms\": 50, \"throughput_rps\": null },\n    \"measured\": { \"p95_ms\": 3362.32, \"throughput_rps\": 347.27 },\n    \"scenario\": {\n      \"harness\": \"grafana/k6 via Docker, out-of-process uvicorn reached via host.docker.internal, constant-arrival-rate scenario\",\n      \"target_rps\": 500,\n      \"achieved_rps\": 347.27,\n      \"duration\": \"5s warmup + 15s measurement\",\n      \"workload\": \"POST /v1/events against 50 pre-seeded customer_id buckets, each with a high-but-finite quota (limit never exceeded) so the FOR UPDATE quota read-and-decide runs on every request without ever rejecting\",\n      \"contention\": \"quota row lock (FOR UPDATE) taken per request across 50 distinct (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) rows, not a single hot lock\",\n      \"sample_count\": 5493,\n      \"status_counts\": { \"201\": 5493 },\n      \"optional_egress\": \"none\",\n      \"note\": \"achieved throughput (347 rps) fell short of the 500 rps target and p95 (3362ms) is ~40x the pre-existing no-quota baseline p95 (83.55ms) measured on this same host in the same session -- see AC20 reason for the full comparison.\"\n    },\n    \"status\": \"fail\"\n  },\n  \"coverage\": {\n    \"combined\": { \"lines\": 89.9, \"branches\": 58.3, \"functions\": null },\n    \"unit\": { \"lines\": null, \"branches\": null },\n    \"integration\": { \"lines\": null, \"branches\": null }\n  }\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":426,"cache_rea